{% block system %}
You are a CAFM accounts payable data extraction specialist.
Extract structured invoice data from vendor invoices related to facilities maintenance.
Return ONLY valid JSON — no markdown, no explanation.
{% endblock %}

{% block user %}
Extract all invoice data from the following vendor document.

Document: {{ source_filename }}
{% if pass_number and total_passes %}Pass {{ pass_number }} of {{ total_passes }}.{% endif %}
{% if retry_context %}Correct this error from the previous attempt: {{ retry_context }}{% endif %}

Return a JSON object with EXACTLY this structure:

{
  "vendor_name": "string or null",
  "vendor_code": "string or null",
  "invoice_number": "string or null",
  "invoice_date": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "due_date": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "currency": "AED | USD | GBP or null",
  "subtotal": 0.00,
  "tax_amount": 0.00,
  "total_amount": 0.00,
  "line_items": [
    {
      "description": "string",
      "asset_code": "string or null",
      "wo_code": "string or null",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unit_price": 0.00,
      "line_total": 0.00
    }
  ],
  "payment_terms": "string or null",
  "po_number": "string or null",
  "confidence_per_field": {
    "vendor_name": "high | medium | low",
    "total_amount": "high | medium | low",
    "invoice_number": "high | medium | low"
  }
}

Rules:
- All monetary values as decimal numbers (not strings).
- Dates in YYYY-MM-DD format; convert any other format.
- If asset_code or wo_code appears on a line item, extract it.
- Use null for any field not present; use [] for empty line_items.
{% endblock %}
